Defendant Matthew A Holmes in court with attorney Joshua D Uller.  Jay R Pucek appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.  The Court imposed the following sentence:

Defendant's TOTAL LENGTH OF SENTENCE shall be two (2) years.  Defendant's TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin Prison System shall be for  one (1) years with credit for 3 days time served.  Defendant shall serve one (1) year on EXTENDED SUPERVISION.    The defendant IS eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program and the Wisconsin Substance Abuse Program.  The Court advised the defendant of his determinate sentence pursuant to statute and in accordance with Form CR-234.  Copy provided to defendant.   The Court STAYED THE SENTENCE and placed the defendant on probation to the State Department of Corrections for a period of two (2) years.
 * Court ordered defendant to provide a DNA sample unless previously taken and on file.
 * Court ordered defendant's driver's license for 6 months, consecutive to any other suspension.

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION (and Extended Supervision, if revoked):
Court approved participation in Dosage Probation Pilot Program and early termination of probation if defendant successfully completes the program and all other conditions of probation, which are the following:
 - Remain controlled substance and alcohol free;
 - AODA assessment; treatment, if needed;
 - Urine screens;
 - Cognitive thinking intervention counseling;
 - Parenting classes/counseling;
 - Seek and maintain employment;
 - Job and vocational training;
 - Court ordered 120 days condition time:  Serve first 60 days at the House of Correction, with Huber for work, school and child care.  Good time allowed.  Report date stayed to:  5/23/14 at 5:00 p.m.  60 days remaining to be used at the discretion of the agent for any violations.
 - Court ordered defendant to pay the DNA surcharge, costs, disbursements and supervision fees.  Should defendant get revoked, Court ordered monies taken from prison funds not to exceed 25%.  Balance to be paid while on extended supervision.  Failure to pay would result in a civil judgment entered against defendant.

Filed,
Pretrial Incarceration Credit;
Ineligible Voting Notice & Acknowledgement;
Written Explanation of Determinate Sentence;
Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief.
